<p>Can I set single constant buffer to multiple locations in D3D11 and OpenGL? What advantages does this approach have? Do I really need this? Can you think of cases where you would use it?</p>  <p>Dreamed example for D3D11:</p>  <pre><code>ID3D11Buffer* bufs[3] = { pBuffer1, pBuffer1, pBuffer1 }; dc-&gt;PSSetConstantBuffers(0, 3, &amp;bufs[0]); </code></pre>  <p>And OpenGL:</p>  <pre><code>glBindBufferBase(GL_UNIFORM_BUFFER, 0, buffer1); glBindBufferBase(GL_UNIFORM_BUFFER, 1, buffer1); glBindBufferBase(GL_UNIFORM_BUFFER, 2, buffer1); </code></pre>